-- HSBC’s Geoghegan to Step Down, Be Replaced by Gulliver, FT Says
-- B y   B e n   L i v e s e y   a n d   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2010-09-23T18:36:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/hsbc-s-geoghegan-to-step-down-from-bank-be-replaced-by-gulliver-ft-says.html
HSBC Holdings Plc Chief Executive
Officer Michael Geoghegan will step down from his post at the
end of the year, the Financial Times reported citing two people
familiar with the matter. Geoghegan will be replaced by
investment banking head Stuart Gulliver and Finance Director
Douglas Flint will be the bank’s new chairman, the newspaper
also said.  HSBC spokesman Adrian Russell declined to comment on the
report by telephone.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net  